        "subject": "LU-19649 ldiskfs: fix error handling in dx_probe/ext4-pdirop.patch",
        "message": "LU-19649 ldiskfs: fix error handling in dx_probe/ext4-pdirop.patch\n\nSince 3ba733f879c2 (\"ext4: avoid cycles in directory h-tree\"),\ndx_probe will check if we have cycles,\nhowever ext4-pdirop.patch handles this differently, most versions\nplace the check for last index level code block in front of the\nupstream change, except for oe2203/ext4-pdirop.patch and\nrhel8.7/ext4-pdirop.patch.\n\nMake all the versions consistent, which checks for cycles first and\nif there's a cycle, release htree spin lock before bailing out.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Li Dongyang <dongyangli@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I93047798ac12715cd2b479c449dac9582755a7f7\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62838\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Jian Yu <yujian@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
